Block 7  →  Build target_h1 … target_h90 anchor columns
Block 8  →  Walk-forward CV splits (no leakage)
Block 9  →  Optuna tuning (10% sample, pruned, 1 fold)
Block 10 →  Train one DART LightGBM per (cluster × horizon)
Block 11 →  Evaluate MAPE / WAPE / bias across all folds
Block 12 →  Predict at anchors → cubic spline → 90 daily forecasts
Block 13 →  Master orchestrator wiring all blocks
When you're ready to extend to CHK and SAV, it's mostly Block 5 (different rolling windows, payroll calendar features) and Block 6 (different cluster count — CHK is more volatile, needs more clusters). CD is a full replacement of Blocks 7–12 with the event classifier. Let me know which you want to tackle next.
